other_tests.findings: Pathological examination revealed a papillary component on the surface and cribriform, irregular, fragmented neoplastic glands associated with a desmoplastic reaction. High-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion and adenocarcinoma in situ (usual type) were also present. A diagnosis of endocervical adenocarcinoma (usual type, grade 2 out of 3, invasive) with squamous intraepithelial lesion and no definitive lymphovascular invasion was made.
The Doppler measurement of blood flow through the middle cerebral artery ranged from 1 to 1.29 multiples of the median on multiple determinations. The Doppler study was reassuring.
Direct antiglobulin testing was positive (with 4+ poly and 4+ IgG and with no C3).
